A special moment while celebrating Mother Earth 🌎 I’m so excited to tell you all about a Project called The One Movement that me and some friends are working on thats all about loving/supporting our planet/our home

For every follow to @theonemovement , we’ll remove 1 plastic water bottle from ocean bound waterways. This is only the beginning and I can’t wait to share more about this incredible movement with you! 
Happy Earth Day xx

Ingredients
1 1/2 ripe banana, mashed
Handful fresh blueberries 
1 tbsp ground flaxseed
1 cup plant milk, unsweetened 
1 tsp Apple cider vinegar
1 cup buckwheat flour
1/2 cup plain coconut yogurt 
1/2 tsp baking soda
1/2 tsp ground cinnamon
1/4 tsp salt
1/2 tsp ground nutmeg 
1 tbsp avocado oil
Maple syrup
Plant butter @miyokoscreamery 
RECIPE

Make a ‘flax egg’ - add 2 1/2 tbsp water to 1 tbsp ground flax, mix, set aside for 5 minutes 
Add vinegar to plant milk, mix, set aside for 5 minutes
Add buckwheat flour, cinnamon, salt, nutmeg, baking soda - mix
Add ‘flax egg’ into milk + vinegar mixture
Add mashed banana + avocado oil 
Mix throughout and then pour into buckwheat mixture 
Add yogurt last! Stir until combined 
Grease griddle and pour in 1/4 cups worth of batter (I used medium heat) 
Serve with butter, syrup and blueberries!

5 garlic , chopped 
1 bell pepper , chopped 
2 zucchini , chopped 
2 squash , chopped 
10 large crimini mushrooms , sliced 
3 sprigs green onion , chopped 
2 large handfuls spinach 
1 1/2 lemon , juiced 
7 oz extra firm tofu, sliced 
1 tbsp grapeseed oil 
2 tbsp Bragg liquid aminos (healthier alternative to soy sauce) 
Toasted black sesame seeds (optional) 
Jalapeño (optional) 
Avocado 
In a large skillet, heat grapeseed oil on low medium
Once hot, add onion and sauté for 2 minutes 
Add garlic and sauté for 1 minute 
Add mushrooms + liquid aminos + lemon juice and turn heat to medium 
Sauté for about 5 minutes 
Add bell pepper + zucchini + squash + green onion and sauté for 3 minutes 
Cover and reduce heat to low - medium 
After 10-15 minutes, add spinach and cover with lid to wilt 
Once wilted remove lid
add a touch more liquid aminos for taste if you like and veggies are ready! 
I stove cooked rice by adding 
1 1/2 cups white + brown rice and 3 cups water
Bringing to a boil
Reducing heat to low and covering with a lid to simmer for 15 minutes (or until rice is cooked) 
Add black sesame seeds as a topping 
In a seasoned cast iron skillet ( or non stick pan if you don’t have a seasoned cast iron) , bring heat to medium
Once hot, add tofu flat 
Let cook untouched for 5 minutes 
Flip
Let cook for another 3 minutes (You can glaze it with a sauce of your choice. I preferred to have it as a texture) 
Remove and serve!

Ingredients:
2 large sweet potatoes (I used white sweet potatoes) 
3-4 tbsp olive oil 
2 tsp dried herbs 
2 tsp black pepper 
2 tsp garlic powder 
1/ 1/2 tsp pink himilayan salt 
3 tsp paprika 
Cilantro for garnish 
Ketchup 
Veganaise 
Spicy mustard 
Recipe:
Scrub and wash your sweet potatoes
With the skin attached, cut sweet potatoes 1/4 inch thick 
In a large mixing bowl combine half olive oil + half spices + half herbs + half sweet potatoes and toss until evenly covered 
Repeat 
Lay fries down flat onto baking sheets
Bake at 425 degrees for 18-20 minutes, turning fries over half way 
When fries are golden, you’re done! 
Let cool and serve with favorite sauce 🌱

Speciesism : the practice of treating members of one species as morally more important than members of other species. 

At the core of our ‘food’ industry 
At the center of the fashion industry 

Embedded inside of nearly every major industry, is this idea that - we as humans - deserve to put ourselves at the center of our own universe. 

Let’s stop inviting products into our lives and homes that pollute the planet, mow down forests, exploit workers, lead to climate and weather crisis around the world and degrade animals in ways we can’t even bare to witness. 

This time in history is pivotal, to see ourselves as a part of the whole. And as much as it can feel overwhelming, see it as a beautiful task to add your unique light. 

Some of the top polluting industries are:
Energy 
Animal Agriculture
Transportation
Fashion 

We grace all of these categories in our daily lives. What an opportunity to create impact. 

What are ways in which you add your light, to be better to Planet Earth?

node.text:
This is me. 
Kin to nature. 
A steward to the Earth. 
A proud mix of many people. 
Tracing back my Indigenous lineage that, like so many others, has been wiped. 
I move forward for peace.
I move forward for truth. 
Chipping away at who I thought I was, to remember who I’ve always been. 

Respects to @merzetti @duyenhuynh @elenapacienza for capturing and creating this authentic moment in time. 

and to @vtmag for sharing this special piece 🦋

Cup of Sunshine, my friends. 🌞 

Recipe: 
 
-fresh grapefruit juice (try this with any of your favorite juices) 
-soaked chia seeds to your liking 
-1 tbsp @healthforcesuperfoods Lucuma Powder 

* Lucuma Powder is low on the Glycemic Index and has a beautiful Maple/Butterscotch/Vanilla flavor and aroma 
* To soak your Chia Seeds add 1/4 cup to 4 cups lightly warmed water. Let sit for 3 minutes then transfer to fridge. You can let them sit 20 minutes - overnight to create a beautiful chia gel
